fields.content:
data:image/png;base64,:image/png;base64, program retrieves from the U.S. Geological Survey the number of earthquakes that have occurred in the past day and then prints out this number. Then, it prints out the magnitude of each of the first five earthquakes, waiting 3 seconds between each print. This program uses iteration (the for loop in the code above) to repeat the print statement multiple times. Feel free to drag and drop blocks from the left panel over to this panel, so that you can add to this program!
